# Epic Willow VIMS Capability Assessment Matrix — Initial Proposed Responses

**Date:** June 9, 2026 (updated June 11, 2026 — external on-hand capture premise; portal scope expansion)
**Purpose:** Pre-populated draft of the [[Epic Willow Inventory Assessment Package]] Section 3 capability matrix. The four previously blank columns (response category, proposed approach, complexity, assumptions/dependencies) are filled in as the **Province's working hypotheses**, derived from the [[Epic Willow Gap Assessment - Alberta Instance Extension]], the [[SBAR - Epic Willow Extension for Provincial Vaccine Depot]], and the two supplied Epic guides (X12 Interface Setup Guide, May 2, 2025; Pharmacy Inventory Management Setup and Support Guide, May 1, 2026).

> **Important framing:** The capability matrix is ultimately Epic's to complete and confirm. These entries are an *initial proposed response* intended to (a) seed Epic's formal response, (b) flag where the Province already has a defensible position from the analysis, and (c) isolate the rows that genuinely require Epic confirmation. Entries marked **⚠ Confirm with Epic** are dependencies the analysis could not resolve from the documents alone.

